{"questionId":"22225465","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, justify that the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> found in part (b)(i) corresponds to a local minimum point on the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;into <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>, clearly leading to positive numerator&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mn>1</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>''</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>therefore this is a local minimum point&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>A0R1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22225465","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.8biii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, justify that the value of x found in part (b)(i) corresponds to a local minimum point on the graph of f.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}